      • register

        protected static void register(Class<?> parent,
                               Class<?> clazz)
        Register a class in the registry. Careful: do not use this from your code before first making sure this has been fully initialized. Otherwise, other implementations will not be found. Therefore, avoid calling this from your own Java code!
        Parameters:
        parent - Class
        clazz - Implementation

        public static List<Class<?>> findAllImplementations(Class<?> c,
                                                    boolean everything,
                                                    boolean parameterizable)
        Find all implementations of a given class in the classpath. Note: returned classes may be abstract.
        Parameters:
        c - Class restriction
        everything - include interfaces, abstract and private classes
        parameterizable - only return classes instantiable by the parameterizable API
        Returns:
        List of found classes.
